# Autonomous RuneScape Task-Based Management Experiment

## Project Vision

Transform the 2009Scape open-source RuneScape server into a management-style automation game where characters execute player-defined tasks instead of requiring constant manual clicks.

https://gitlab.com/2009scape/2009scape

The system should allow players to assign goals such as gathering resources, training skills, or completing objectives while the character autonomously performs the required actions.

This project will be used privately by the team as an experimental sandbox for exploring automation, AI agents, and management-style gameplay layered on top of a RuneScape-like world simulation.

---

# Core Concept

Instead of:

"Click tree -> wait -> click tree -> wait"

The player issues **tasks**.

Examples:

* Cut 500 logs
* Reach Woodcutting level 30
* Mine 200 iron ore
* Train fishing until level 40
* Craft 1000 runes

The game engine manages the character's behaviour until the objective is complete.

---

# Design Pillars

## 1 Automation-First Gameplay

The game should play itself once tasks are assigned.

## 2 Strategic Planning

Players manage long-term goals rather than performing repetitive actions.

## 3 System Transparency

Players should clearly see why their character makes decisions.

## 4 Expandable Automation

Tasks should be expandable into more complex automation chains later.

Example future chain:

Mine ore -> Smelt bars -> Smith weapons -> Sell weapons

---

# Core Systems Overview

## Task System

Defines player goals and monitors completion conditions.

## Behaviour Engine

Chooses the actions required to complete the current task.

## World Interaction Layer

Handles movement, interactions, and animations.

## Resource Tracking

Tracks inventory, bank contents, and progress.

## Planning Logic

Determines the optimal way to complete a task.

